Barcelona's star Lionel Messi scores twice against Real Betis, his 85th and 86th goals in a calendar year, breaking the record created by German legend Gerd Müller (85 goals) in 1972. (ESPN) (Goal.com) (BBC) (Reuters)In the UEFA Group H, Montenegro secures a 1–1 draw against England in Podgorica. (BBC) (FIFA)In Alpine skiing, Austrian Marcel Hirscher and Slovenian Tina Maze win the overall men's and women's 2013 Alpine Skiing World Cup titles, respectively. (AP via Yahoo! News)